@page "/polling"

<PageTitle>Polling - ReactiveBlazor Demo</PageTitle>

<div class="space-y-6">
    <!-- Page header -->
    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-center justify-between border-b border-base-300 pb-4 gap-4">
        <div>
            <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-base-content">Polling (Auto-Refresh)</h1>
            <p class="text-sm text-base-content/60 mt-1">
                A live metrics dashboard that refreshes itself on a timer — no clicks required.
                Each tick reuses the normal dispatch pipeline, so it also fans out an OOB signal
                to the activity log on the right.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="badge badge-accent badge-outline font-semibold gap-2 py-3 px-4">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M4 4v5h.582m15.356 2A8.001 8.001 0 004.582 9m0 0H9m11 11v-5h-.581m0 0a8.003 8.003 0 01-15.357-2m15.357 2H15" />
            </svg>
            Polling Demo
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <!-- The polling dashboard (its own reactive component). -->
        <PollingDashboard />

        <!-- OOB subscriber: re-rendered by the MetricsSampled signal each tick publishes. -->
        <PollingActivityLog />
    </div>

    <!-- How it works -->
    <div class="card bg-base-100 border border-base-300 shadow-sm">
        <div class="card-body p-5">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-base mb-3">How it works</h3>
            <ul class="text-sm text-base-content/70 space-y-1.5 list-disc list-inside">
                <li>
                    <code>&lt;ReactiveRoot PollAction="Sample" PollInterval="@@(IsLive ? 2000 : 0)"&gt;</code>
                    emits <code>data-poll</code> / <code>data-poll-interval</code> on the root div.
                </li>
                <li>The client runtime starts a timer that fires the <code>Sample</code> action every tick — reusing queuing, busy-state, and DOM morphing.</li>
                <li><strong>Stop polling</strong> sets <code>PollInterval</code> to 0; the attributes vanish on the next morph and the client clears the timer automatically.</li>
                <li>Each tick publishes <code>MetricsSampled</code>, so the OOB activity log updates in the same response (open DevTools → Network to watch the dispatches).</li>
                <li>Polling pauses while the browser tab is hidden and resumes when it regains focus.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
